gemini_pro.summary:
The Knowledge Graph is highly accurate regarding dimensions, airflows, and cartridge/module counts, with a 100% match on complex tables for GDC, GDMI, and GDP. The primary discrepancies are found in the material availability for accessories (TT and PT transitions) where the graph omits stainless/aluzink options shown in the PDF icons.

A specific data error exists in the weights for the largest sizes of the GDB family (Width 1500 and 1800), where the graph consistently under-reports weight compared to the PDF. Additionally, construction metadata placeholders need to be finalized based on the clear 'single-wall' descriptions in the catalog.

findings.description: Graph anger 900/950-varianten som 'max filter depth 600mm'. PDF för GDC säger att längd 900/950 kan vara för 450 mm cylinder + polisfilter eller för 600 mm cylinder. Det är inte samma sak som 'max filter depth 600mm' utan kräver variantlogik (polisfilter vs cylinderlängd).

anthropic_opus.summary:
The Knowledge Graph captures the majority of the MANN+HUMMEL HVAC filter housing catalog with reasonable accuracy. All 12 product families from the PDF (GDP, GDB, GDMI, GDC, GDC FLEX, GDMI FLEX, BFF, PFF, PT, TT, EXL, Filter Profil) are present in the graph. The dimension tables for GDP (35 sizes), GDB (27 sizes), GDMI (37 sizes), GDC (12 sizes), GDC FLEX (6 sizes), GDMI FLEX (8 sizes), BFF (5 sizes), PFF (25 sizes), PT (5 sizes), TT (35 sizes), EXL (8 sizes), and Filter Profil (12 widths × 3 depths) are largely complete and match the PDF. Material availability is correctly differentiated per family, with GDMI and GDMI FLEX correctly restricted from stainless steel variants.

The most critical issues found are: (1) GDB 1800x900 short weight is stored as 63 kg instead of the correct 36 kg from the PDF; (2) GDMI length variant references are stored as '600/900 & 850' instead of the correct '600/650 & 850/900'; (3) GDMI 2100x900 half-module count appears to be 4 in the graph versus 3 in the PDF; and (4) several construction type values are marked as 'PENDING_MIKAEL' indicating unverified data. The weight column labeling for GDMI uses '1100' which should be '850/900'.

Overall, the graph is a solid foundation with approximately 85-90% data accuracy. The primary areas needing attention are: correcting the specific weight and module count errors identified, verifying construction types that are still pending, ensuring default materials are correctly flagged for all families, and cleaning up orphaned CapacityRule nodes. The enrichment data (applications, environments, stressors) adds value beyond the PDF but should be clearly sourced separately.

final_report.summary:
The MANN+HUMMEL HVAC filter housing knowledge graph captures the core product catalog structure with reasonable accuracy. All 12 product families from the PDF are represented, and the dimensional tables (sizes, airflows, module/cartridge counts) are largely correct for GDP, GDB, GDMI, GDC, GDC FLEX, GDMI FLEX, BFF, PFF, PT, TT, EXL, and Filter Profil. Material availability is correctly differentiated per family in most cases, with GDMI and GDMI FLEX properly restricted from stainless steel variants.

However, the audit identified 25 findings across several critical areas. The most impactful issues are: (1) garbled GDMI length variant references ('600/900 & 850' instead of '600/650 & 850/900'), (2) a weight data error for GDB 1800x900, (3) unverified construction type metadata marked as PENDING_MIKAEL/BOLTED when the PDF clearly specifies single-wall or double-wall construction, and (4) missing material exclusion constraints that could allow invalid stainless steel selections for GDMI families. The graph also lacks proper modeling of the dual-purpose 900/950mm length variants for carbon filter cabinets (GDC, GDC FLEX) where the same length serves both 450mm+polisfilter and 600mm cylinder configurations.

The graph's metadata layer needs the most attention: material availability should distinguish standard from on-request options, corrosion class modeling should separate product environment class from material class, and ungrounded data (Max Chlorine PPM) should be removed or re-sourced. The enrichment data (applications, environments) adds value but should be clearly tagged as non-catalog-sourced. With the recommended corrections applied, the graph would achieve an estimated accuracy of 88-92%.
